GateDocument.TextWithNodes: The Luzon earthquake occurred on Monday, July 16, 1990 , at 4:26 PM local time in the Philippines . The densely populated island of Luzon was struck by an earthquake with a 7.8 Ms (surface-wave magnitude). An estimated 1,621 people were killed in the earthquake, most of the fatalities located in Central Luzon and the Cordillera region .
